In [30]:
def function(x):
    return x**2

def central_difference(f, x, h):
    x2 = x+h 
    x3 = x-h
    derivada = (f(x2)-f(x3))/(2*h)
    return derivada
In [31]:
print (f"The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.1 is {central_difference(function, 2, 0.1)}")
print (f"The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.01 is {central_difference(function, 2, 0.01)}")
print (f"The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.001 is {central_difference(function, 2, 0.001)}")

The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.1 is 4.000000000000001
The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.01 is 3.999999999999937
The derivative of f(x) = x^2 at x = 2 using h = 0.001 is 3.9999999999995595
